25:16.181 --> 25:17.098
I'm just kidding.

25:17.182 --> 25:19.184
{\an1}I'm just kidding.
Don't worry.

25:20.852 --> 25:22.771
Can't believe I get
to live here now.

25:22.854 --> 25:23.939
Well, you're in charge now,
Oliver--

25:24.022 --> 25:25.774
uh, Mr. President.

25:25.857 --> 25:26.942
You're the leader

25:27.025 --> 25:28.318
of the free world.

25:28.401 --> 25:31.154
Well... as leader
of the free world,

25:31.238 --> 25:33.657
we need to fulfill
my campaign promises.

25:33.740 --> 25:35.951
{\an3}ASAP.

25:33.740 --> 25:35.951
Absolutely.

25:36.034 --> 25:40.205
First off, free video games
for every American.

25:40.288 --> 25:42.123
Nintendo, PlayStation,

25:42.207 --> 25:43.750
whatever they want.

25:43.833 --> 25:44.793
{\an3}Um...

25:44.876 --> 25:46.544
(chuckles) Oliver...

25:46.628 --> 25:49.464
Honey, I don't think that we can
quite just do that.

25:49.548 --> 25:51.258
What are you talking about, Mom?

25:51.341 --> 25:53.009
{\an1}Well, I mean that
there are laws.

25:53.093 --> 25:54.469
{\an1}Congress.

25:54.552 --> 25:57.347
(whispering): We talked
about this, remember, honey?

25:57.430 --> 25:59.391
{\an3}But I promised
everyone video games,

25:59.474 --> 26:01.643
{\an3}and you, Mr.
Chief of Staff,

26:01.726 --> 26:03.520
{\an3}are gonna make
sure that happens.

26:03.603 --> 26:05.981
{\an3}Well, I'm not quite sure
that Congress is gonna

26:06.064 --> 26:08.275
{\an3}go for that, Mr.
President, especially

26:08.358 --> 26:10.193
{\an1}given the way the national
debt looks right now.

26:10.277 --> 26:12.320
{\an3}And plus, companies aren't
just going to willingly

26:12.404 --> 26:13.655
give away their games.

26:13.738 --> 26:15.156
Guess they'll just have to.

26:15.240 --> 26:16.616
{\an6}Yes, but...

26:15.240 --> 26:16.616
But nothing.

26:16.700 --> 26:18.326
They have to.

26:18.410 --> 26:20.036
I made a promise.

26:20.120 --> 26:24.708
So, they give away
270 million games

26:24.791 --> 26:28.670
to every American,
or we put a surcharge tax

26:28.753 --> 26:30.547
of a million dollars a Game Boy

26:30.630 --> 26:32.674
and put them out of business
in a day.

26:32.757 --> 26:37.053
The people voted. We have
to give 'em what we promised.

26:39.931 --> 26:43.184
{\an5}Hey, Oliver.

26:39.931 --> 26:43.184
Mr. President.

26:43.268 --> 26:45.145
Sorry, Raff, but it sounds
really cool.

26:45.228 --> 26:47.272
You're right.

26:47.355 --> 26:49.858
Mr. President, maybe we should,
uh, hold off

26:49.941 --> 26:52.569
on the video game thing
until you get settled in...

26:52.652 --> 26:55.655
I'm settled in, Raff,
and I know what I want.

26:55.739 --> 26:58.074
And you guys are gonna
get that done for me

26:58.158 --> 27:00.869
or I'll get <i> other</i> people
to get it done for me.

27:00.952 --> 27:03.204
There won't be a shortage
of people who want to work

27:03.288 --> 27:06.082
for the new president
of the United States.

27:08.084 --> 27:10.837
Now... where's
the White House kitchen?

27:10.920 --> 27:14.174
I want a triple-scoop
chocolate chip mint,

27:14.257 --> 27:17.177
vanilla and coffee ice cream
sundae with whipped cream,

27:17.260 --> 27:19.596
chocolate sauce and sprinkles!

27:19.679 --> 27:21.598
(door opens)

27:21.681 --> 27:22.974
(door closes)

27:27.562 --> 27:29.564
(chirping)

27:31.858 --> 27:33.902
{\an5}OLIVER:
I want to make a new vlog
of me singing

27:33.985 --> 27:36.404
and all these dancers around me
dressed like soldiers.

27:36.488 --> 27:38.907
Mm-hmm. I'm not sure if vlogging
is the best way to communicate.

27:38.990 --> 27:40.200
Of course it is.

27:40.283 --> 27:42.410
{\an3}I want to sing
about world peace.

27:42.494 --> 27:43.953
The lyrics should
be something like,

27:44.037 --> 27:46.081
"Either you're with peace,

27:46.164 --> 27:48.124
or you're not,"

27:48.208 --> 27:50.502
and if they're not, we start
to kill off all the dancers.

27:50.585 --> 27:51.586
{\an3}SENIOR AIDE:
Um...

27:51.669 --> 27:52.545
I mean, not for real, obviously.

27:52.629 --> 27:54.923
{\an3}But in the video,
all bloody and stuff.

27:55.006 --> 27:55.924
It'll be cool.

27:56.007 --> 27:58.635
{\an1}(barking)

27:58.718 --> 28:01.096
{\an1}Dog selection today,
Mr. President.

28:01.179 --> 28:02.305
Finally!

28:02.389 --> 28:05.642
Hi. Hello!
Oh, yes, you are so sweet.

28:05.725 --> 28:07.811
Hey, come here, come here.

28:07.894 --> 28:09.604
Okay, no. No.

28:09.687 --> 28:11.398
No. Maybe.

28:11.481 --> 28:12.982
{\an3}No.

28:13.066 --> 28:14.901
Maybe. No. (gasps)

28:14.984 --> 28:16.986
This one!
This guy right here!

28:17.070 --> 28:18.113
No, no, no, this one.

28:18.196 --> 28:21.783
He's perfect.
My new Homer.

28:21.866 --> 28:23.076
It's a female dog, sir.

28:23.159 --> 28:24.577
{\an3}What? Ew!

28:24.661 --> 28:26.121
What were you thinking?

28:26.204 --> 28:27.622
{\an5}I thought, um...

28:26.204 --> 28:27.622
Thought what?

28:27.705 --> 28:28.957
I want a new Homer!

28:29.040 --> 28:31.000
Does Homer sound like
a girl's name to you?

28:31.084 --> 28:32.794
Well, there's other
dogs here, sir.

28:32.877 --> 28:34.504
{\an3}Get rid of 'em.
I don't want 'em.

28:34.587 --> 28:36.631
Um, sir? These dogs were
selected from the pound.

28:36.714 --> 28:39.175
I don't really care.
I don't want them.

28:39.259 --> 28:42.303
{\an6}SENIOR AIDE:
Okay. It is, however,
time for your physical.

28:42.387 --> 28:44.305
Physical? No way.

28:44.389 --> 28:46.099
{\an3}Well, I'm sorry, Mr. President,
but Congress requires

28:46.182 --> 28:48.726
{\an3}that the president
get a yearly physical.

28:48.810 --> 28:49.561
Well, then fire Congress.

28:49.644 --> 28:51.855
{\an3}SENIOR AIDE:
We can't quite do that.

28:51.938 --> 28:53.064
{\an3}Well, I'm not gonna
see any doctor.

28:53.148 --> 28:54.482
Especially an old man doctor.

28:54.566 --> 28:56.109
Okay, but it's scheduled
for today, so...

28:56.192 --> 28:57.652
{\an3}Well, then
<i>un-schedule it.</i>

28:57.735 --> 28:59.904
{\an3}And never
<i>reschedule</i> it.

28:59.988 --> 29:03.158
That's the only real schedule
I can get behind.

29:03.241 --> 29:05.952
And make a new law:
no old doctors.

29:06.035 --> 29:07.287
Everyone okay with that?

29:10.748 --> 29:12.500
I said, is everyone
okay with that?

29:12.584 --> 29:14.544
Yes, Mr. President.

29:14.627 --> 29:15.753
OTHERS:
Yes, Mr. President.

29:18.131 --> 29:19.632
{\an5}Think fast! (laughs)

29:18.131 --> 29:19.632
{\an3}(grunts)

29:19.716 --> 29:22.051
{\an6}He got me.

29:19.716 --> 29:22.051
You lose, you lose.

29:22.135 --> 29:24.637
{\an6}(chuckling):
He got me.

29:22.135 --> 29:24.637
Think fast! (yells)

29:26.097 --> 29:28.183
{\an4}Mr. Chairman, Mitch.
Can...?

29:26.097 --> 29:28.183
What is it, Raff?

29:28.266 --> 29:29.684
{\an3}President wants
a military parade

29:29.767 --> 29:30.768
{\an3}for his sister's
birthday next week.

29:30.852 --> 29:32.395
{\an3}I am knee-deep in donkey
shit trying to organize it.

29:32.479 --> 29:34.814
{\an4}Right, uh,
can I...?

29:32.479 --> 29:34.814
What? Can I what?

29:35.690 --> 29:37.692
{\an4}Can I get a minute
with you?

29:35.690 --> 29:37.692
{\an3}(exhales)

29:37.775 --> 29:40.236
{\an3}What is it, Raff? You've
been out of sorts for weeks.

29:40.320 --> 29:41.529
Um...

29:41.613 --> 29:42.906
(clicks tongue)

29:45.950 --> 29:47.202
Aren't you a little worried?

29:47.285 --> 29:48.536
I'm always worried.

29:48.620 --> 29:49.996
What's your problem?

29:50.079 --> 29:51.039
{\an5}(bell ringing)

29:50.079 --> 29:51.039
{\an1}OLIVER:
Get out of the way!

29:51.122 --> 29:53.708
Mr. President coming through!
Get out of my way!

29:54.751 --> 29:57.045
{\an5}(laughing): Hey.

29:54.751 --> 29:57.045
Hey.

29:57.128 --> 29:58.213
{\an3}Choo-choo!

29:58.296 --> 29:59.797
{\an5}(women gasp)

29:58.296 --> 29:59.797
{\an3}Move it!

29:59.881 --> 30:03.051
{\an3}Hey, order pizza
for everyone.

30:03.134 --> 30:05.845
Don't you think
the president seems like a...?

30:05.929 --> 30:07.597
{\an5}A kid.

30:05.929 --> 30:07.597
Right.

30:07.680 --> 30:10.225
Like a spoiled kid. Like a...

30:11.309 --> 30:13.228
...like the most spoiled kid

30:13.311 --> 30:15.146
in the history of the world,
you know?

30:15.230 --> 30:17.232
He's commander-in-chief,
this is the greatest country

30:17.315 --> 30:18.566
in the world.
President says "Jump,"

30:18.650 --> 30:19.859
I say "How high?"

30:19.943 --> 30:21.110
{\an3}I don't care
that he's a kid.

30:21.194 --> 30:22.362
Approval rating's
through the roof,

30:22.445 --> 30:23.571
everybody loves
their video games.

30:23.655 --> 30:25.198
Strange time to be
talking treason,

30:25.281 --> 30:26.491
{\an3}Hanks.

30:26.574 --> 30:27.450
Treason?

30:27.534 --> 30:29.244
{\an5}Treason.

30:27.534 --> 30:29.244
No, I-I'm not

30:29.327 --> 30:31.204
{\an5}talking treason.
I'm, I'm not...

30:29.327 --> 30:31.204
Sure sounds like it.

30:31.287 --> 30:33.122
And I don't like it
and I won't have it.

30:33.206 --> 30:34.916
Understood?

30:34.999 --> 30:36.626
Understood.

30:36.709 --> 30:38.336
Good.

30:41.965 --> 30:43.883
(Helen speaks
indistinctly)

30:43.967 --> 30:44.968
(chuckling)

30:43.967 --> 30:44.968
Helen.

30:45.051 --> 30:47.095
{\an1}Hey.

30:45.051 --> 30:47.095
{\an3}Helen.

30:47.178 --> 30:50.014
Oliver's not the president,
you are the real president.

30:50.098 --> 30:52.100
Don't you think it's time
you intervened?

30:52.183 --> 30:54.435
Intervene?

30:55.478 --> 30:57.438
{\an1}(chuckles)
Why would I do that?

30:57.522 --> 31:01.150
Raff, everything you said
would come true has.

31:01.234 --> 31:02.777
He connects with people.

31:02.860 --> 31:04.279
{\an1}My child.

31:04.362 --> 31:05.947
He touches people.

31:06.030 --> 31:09.993
Intervening's the last thing
I'm gonna do.

31:18.376 --> 31:20.461
{\an6}MAURA:
I say if it's bothering
you that much,

31:20.545 --> 31:21.713
you should just
talk with him.

31:21.796 --> 31:23.464
{\an1}RAFF:
Okay, it's just hard to know

31:23.548 --> 31:25.967
{\an1}what to say to an 11-year-old
who's also the president.

31:26.050 --> 31:27.760
{\an3}Well, you've done
pretty good thus far.

31:27.844 --> 31:29.846
{\an1}(sighs): Yeah.
It was easier before.

31:30.680 --> 31:33.808
{\an3}Listen, we're
mercenaries, right?

31:33.891 --> 31:35.852
I mean, that's what we are.

31:35.935 --> 31:37.645
{\an3}Your big mistake
was staying

31:37.729 --> 31:39.272
{\an3}with him in the
White House.

31:39.355 --> 31:40.690
{\an3}You should have
followed me.

31:40.773 --> 31:43.651
{\an3}And I moved on and
business is booming.

31:43.735 --> 31:46.279
{\an3}Didn't have to stick
around and have regrets,

31:46.362 --> 31:49.157
{\an3}see how the
sausage is made.

31:49.240 --> 31:50.825
{\an1}It's just, no one seems
to be willing

31:50.908 --> 31:52.285
{\an1}to confront him,
you know?

31:52.368 --> 31:54.162
{\an1}Even his parents
seem cowed.

31:54.245 --> 31:55.955
{\an3}Well, maybe
they are cowed.

31:56.039 --> 31:57.832
{\an3}Or maybe everyone's
okay with it.

31:57.915 --> 31:59.500
{\an3}I mean, sure, he's
a little bit bratty,

31:59.584 --> 32:01.836
but so are a lot of
kids, it's a phase.

32:01.919 --> 32:03.171
{\an3}Like your
chamomile tea phase,

32:03.254 --> 32:04.839
it's gonna pass.

32:04.922 --> 32:06.716
{\an3}Raff, you of
all people knew

32:06.799 --> 32:08.134
what you were
getting into

32:08.217 --> 32:10.219
{\an3}when you decided to
run his campaign.

32:10.303 --> 32:12.847
{\an3}Try and enjoy
this moment

32:12.930 --> 32:15.350
{\an3}instead of
worrying so much.

32:15.433 --> 32:17.018
You're the conquering hero.

32:17.101 --> 32:18.686
Right?

32:18.770 --> 32:21.648
One of the most famous
campaign managers in history.

32:21.731 --> 32:26.361
{\an3}The man who got Oliver
Foley elected president.

32:30.448 --> 32:31.866
{\an3}Thanks.

32:33.326 --> 32:35.286
<i>(Raff panting)</i>

32:35.370 --> 32:37.038
I tried to do the right thing...

32:37.121 --> 32:39.040
for once.

32:39.123 --> 32:42.043
{\an5}(loud beeping)

32:39.123 --> 32:42.043
{\an1}ORDERLY:
Mr. Hanks.

32:42.126 --> 32:44.420
We're losing him.
Get the crash cart in here.

32:59.519 --> 33:01.688
{\an3}You distracted
me, Raff.

33:01.771 --> 33:02.939
{\an1}Oh, sorry.

33:03.022 --> 33:04.232
{\an3}OLIVER:
It's okay.

33:04.315 --> 33:06.025
I never get a hole-in-one.

33:06.109 --> 33:08.111
And it sucks.

33:09.696 --> 33:10.905
Want to play?

33:10.988 --> 33:12.615
Could use the company.
My sister has homework

33:12.699 --> 33:15.076
and the Secretary
of Homeland Security

33:15.159 --> 33:16.994
sucks at golf.

33:18.996 --> 33:20.707
Um, sure, thank you.

33:25.545 --> 33:27.255
I think Nixon put
in the golf thing.

33:27.338 --> 33:29.298
{\an6}But it's so
boring, putting.

33:27.338 --> 33:29.298
Mm-hmm.

33:29.382 --> 33:31.884
{\an3}Who wants to
just putt?

33:31.968 --> 33:33.928
I want windmills
and pirate ships.

33:34.011 --> 33:35.263
{\an3}Those little pencils
to keep track.

33:35.346 --> 33:36.848
Right.

33:39.267 --> 33:41.269
(sharp exhale)

33:43.312 --> 33:45.064
{\an5}Can I speak candidly?

33:43.312 --> 33:45.064
I don't know.

33:45.148 --> 33:46.399
{\an3}Can you?

33:49.527 --> 33:52.071
Um, I'm a little worried.

33:52.155 --> 33:54.615
So am I, actually.

33:54.699 --> 33:56.743
What do you mean?

34:00.037 --> 34:01.664
{\an3}I mean...

34:01.748 --> 34:03.791
{\an3}this treason thing's
pretty serious.

34:06.043 --> 34:08.920
{\an3}You like the lighting?
I think it's cool.

34:09.005 --> 34:10.922
I'm not being
treasonous, Oliver.

34:11.007 --> 34:12.341
I'm just worried
about a few things.

34:12.425 --> 34:13.967
There is a difference.

34:14.051 --> 34:16.137
{\an5}Hit your ball, Raff.

34:14.051 --> 34:16.137
Oliver.

34:16.219 --> 34:17.513
{\an3}Putt.

34:28.733 --> 34:31.110
{\an3}Not bad.

34:31.194 --> 34:32.820
{\an3}My turn.

34:34.781 --> 34:35.782
{\an3}(grunts)

34:35.864 --> 34:37.158
Thing is, Raff...

34:37.241 --> 34:39.118
you were
my first real supporter.

34:39.202 --> 34:42.580
Hurts me that you're
not fully backing me.

34:45.500 --> 34:47.752
Fuck! I never get it in

34:47.835 --> 34:49.378
on the first try!

34:49.462 --> 34:51.589
Oliver, I do back you.

34:51.672 --> 34:53.632
{\an5}I just think that the...

34:51.672 --> 34:53.632
No.

34:53.716 --> 34:55.176
You don't get to think.

34:55.259 --> 34:58.304
You just back me.
You back me unconditionally.

34:58.387 --> 35:00.640
Whatever happened to surrounding
yourself with the greatest minds

35:00.723 --> 35:02.683
so that you could get
the most informed opinions?

35:02.767 --> 35:04.227
That was your idea.

35:04.310 --> 35:06.395
Your line in that commercial
about my dying dog.

35:08.272 --> 35:09.774
My dog's dying, Raff.

35:09.857 --> 35:11.192
He's dying.

35:11.275 --> 35:12.693
I'm such a good actor.

35:12.777 --> 35:15.154
I just pretended
Homer was dying.

35:15.238 --> 35:17.365
Just to get you
back on my team.

35:17.448 --> 35:19.534
No!

35:19.617 --> 35:21.160
I want a hole-in-one!

35:25.039 --> 35:27.458
There! Hole-in-one!
I win!

35:28.626 --> 35:30.044
That's not the way it works.

35:30.127 --> 35:32.380
It isn't?

35:32.463 --> 35:33.714
No.

35:33.798 --> 35:35.550
I said it was
a hole-in-one.

35:35.633 --> 35:36.926
And I'm president.

35:37.009 --> 35:39.720
Do you support me
or are you treasonous?

35:48.020 --> 35:50.064
I'm not treasonous, Oliver.

35:50.147 --> 35:52.859
Mr. President.

35:52.942 --> 35:56.362
"I'm not treasonous,
Mr. President."

35:59.365 --> 36:01.784
I'm not treasonous,
Mr. President.

36:01.868 --> 36:03.536
Good.

36:03.619 --> 36:06.080
So, it was a hole-in-one, right?

36:09.333 --> 36:11.627
No.

36:11.711 --> 36:13.796
No, it wasn't.

36:16.299 --> 36:19.635
It was not a hole-in-one,
Oliver.

36:26.225 --> 36:27.810
Gun!

36:27.894 --> 36:29.228
There's a gun! Shoot him.

36:35.026 --> 36:36.944
{\an5}REPORTER
<i>What do you think</i>
<i>about Raff Hanks?</i>

36:37.028 --> 36:40.448
{\an8}Oh, I think he's
the worst scum of the earth.

36:40.531 --> 36:43.242
{\an8}How dare he try and attack
that sweet little boy?

36:43.326 --> 36:45.745
{\an8}The president dodged a bullet.
Literally.

36:45.828 --> 36:46.871
{\an8}Raff Hanks got what he deserved.

36:46.954 --> 36:48.497
{\an8}He got what he deserved.

36:46.954 --> 36:48.497
{\an8}Raff Hanks got what he deserved.

36:48.581 --> 36:49.248
{\an8}Raff Hanks...

36:48.581 --> 36:49.248
{\an8}Raff Hanks...

36:49.332 --> 36:50.333
{\an8}Raff Hanks got...

36:49.332 --> 36:50.333
{\an8}...got...

36:50.416 --> 36:51.792
{\an8}<i>...got what he deserved.</i>

36:51.876 --> 36:54.253
Glad to see you awake,
Mr. Hanks.

36:54.337 --> 36:55.838
Was afraid we lost you there.

36:55.922 --> 36:58.674
{\an5}What?

36:55.922 --> 36:58.674
You need an operation

36:58.758 --> 37:00.801
on a ruptured spleen
and a punctured lung.

37:00.885 --> 37:03.930
The president has asked for
his very own doctor to help you.

37:04.013 --> 37:05.848
You're not the doctor?

37:05.932 --> 37:08.267
{\an1}The law does not permit me
to be a doctor.

37:08.351 --> 37:09.977
The doctor will be
with you shortly.

37:10.061 --> 37:12.104
(monitor beeping)

37:14.565 --> 37:16.484
All right.

37:16.567 --> 37:18.778
Let's get this done quick,
mister.

37:18.861 --> 37:20.446
No.

37:20.529 --> 37:22.657
(Raff panting)

37:22.740 --> 37:23.991
{\an3}No.

37:24.075 --> 37:26.786
I want to finish my video games.

37:26.869 --> 37:28.663
No! No!

37:28.746 --> 37:30.831
(grunting)

37:30.915 --> 37:32.959
(screaming)

37:34.919 --> 37:37.338
Society is a fragile ecosystem.

37:37.421 --> 37:41.050
Razzle and dazzle people
